Then, combine 2-3 cooked ingredients that make sense together in real life (e.g., cooked protein + cooked grain, or cooked protein + cooked vegetable) to reach values of 40-80. Avoid combining too many items (more than 3-4 components) or using tools on already complex dishes, as this frequently leads to 'overcomplicated' or 'overcooked' items with zero or negative value. Submit when you reach a score of 60-80 to secure a good score, as trying to go higher is very risky.
